      "descriptions": [
        "<b>ELIXIR</b> is a European life sciences infrastructure that brings together and coordinates various types of scientific resources helping researchers to access, analyse and share life science data, and promote the exchange of expertise. The European countries that are members of ELIXIR form a “Node”, which is a network of research organisations that work within that member state. <br/> In the light of the large amounts of complex data generated in life sciences, data findability and reusability are of pivotal importance, while aligning with FAIR data principles. To this end, ELIXIR has collaborated with the <b>Global Alliance for Genomics and Health (GA4GH)</b> to drive the implementation of <b>Beacon technology</b> across ELIXIR Nodes. The Beacon v2 protocol, which has been adopted as a GA4GH standard, is a simple data discovery tool that allows researchers to search genomic and biomedical data worldwide without compromising confidentiality or ownership of the datasets. The individual Beacon instances are then aggregated into the ELIXIR Beacon Network as part of the ELIXIR infrastructure service to facilitate and encourage data sharing by the Nodes."
      ],
